Package IITCarPark

IITCarPark is a set of classes that represent the IIT car park system

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EntryQueueRunnable
    Class that Implements the Runnable interface This class is used to create a thread which simulates vehicles forming a queue in front of a particular entrance in the car park in the IITCarParkSimulator class
    EntryRunnable
    Class that Implements the Runnable interface This class is used to create a thread which simulates vehicles entering a car park from a particular entrance queue in the IITCarParkSimulator class
    ExitRunnable
    Class that Implements the Runnable interface This class is used to create a thread which simulates vehicles leaving a car park in the IITCarParkSimulator class
    IITCarParkManager
    Class that implements the CarParkManager interface The main functionality is to simulate the car park manager of the IIT car park.
    IITCarParkSimulator
    Class that is used to run a Simulation of the IIT car park The Class simulates vehicles forming queues, vehicles entering and leaving from each entrance
    IITParkingMeter
    Class that calculates the parking costs in the IITCarParkManager class
    Main
    Class that runs the car park application

Package IITCarPark Description

IITCarPark is a set of classes that represent the IIT car park system
